-- Kroton Rallies Most Since August After Deal: Sao Paulo Mover
-- B y   K a t e r i n a   P e t r o f f
-- 2012-05-29T18:12:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/kroton-rallies-most-since-august-after-deal-sao-paulo-mover.html
Kroton Educacional SA (KROT11) , a Brazilian
education company, gained the most in nine months after
announcing a  seventh  acquisition in a year.  Units  gained  5.1 percent to 28.80 reais at 2:15 p.m. in  Sao
Paulo , the highest level on a closing basis since May 8. The
increase was the biggest since Aug. 30.  Kroton said in a regulatory filing today that its unit
Editora e Distribuidora Educacional SA acquired Grupo Uniasselvi
for 510 million reais ($255 million).  Estacio Participacoes SA (ESTC3) , a competitor, also announced an
acquisition, saying in a regulatory filing yesterday that it
agreed to buy UB Unisaoluis Educacional SA for 28 million reais
in cash and debt.  Estacio was little changed, while  Anhanguera Educacional
Participacoes SA (AEDU3)  jumped 3.3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
